Descriptions_WS_WA: Walla Walla wiped out by freeze; rest of state solid
Ripe flavors but non excessively heavy
Hot summer and cool autumn made rich; balanced wines
Cool summer and warm autumn; many great wines
Late year with early frost made fine Merlot and Syrah
Cool year produced crisp reds with lovely ripe flavors
Another cool year; moderate alcohols with crisp balance
Ideal conditions produced powerful wines with elegance
hot growing season produced wines of generosity, with ripe flavors; best achieve balance
Hot, sunny gowing season yielded full-bodied reds with ripe falvors and formidable tannins
A warm spring gave way to a moderate summer, promising balanced but structured wines
A cool, wet spring led to a hot summer, but moderate weather near harvest helped build expression
Cool autumn weather salvaged an otherwise hot year, making for full-bodied yet well-balance wines
